      "text": "A 27-year-old man presents with acute left upper quadrant pain after being struck in the abdomen during a basketball game. He is pale and diaphoretic. Vital signs: BP 86/52 mmHg, HR 128 bpm, RR 24/min, SpO2 95% on room air. He has a history of mononucleosis diagnosed 3 weeks ago. Examination shows abdominal distention and tenderness with guarding. Focused assessment with sonography for trauma (FAST) demonstrates free intraperitoneal fluid. What is the most appropriate next step in management?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "CT scan of the abdomen and pelvis with IV contrast"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Admission for observation with serial hemoglobin checks/p&gt;"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Immediate surgical consultation for laparotomy"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Transfusion of platelets and consult hematology"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Administration of corticosteroids for splenic inflammation"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>CT abdomen with IV contrast may identify <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Bh0zTf&anker=Zfdae7b2ea943f3b332fdf4c3cf7cb8c3\" data-learningcard-id=\"Bh0zTf\" data-anker=\"Zfdae7b2ea943f3b332fdf4c3cf7cb8c3\">splenic injury</a>, but this patient is <span data-sememe-id=\"3LdSxq0\">hemodynamically unstable</span>. In unstable <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4N03Yg&anker=Ze99c35011e3521f2455031319e96fe10\" data-learningcard-id=\"4N03Yg\" data-anker=\"Ze99c35011e3521f2455031319e96fe10\">trauma patients</a> with positive <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4N03Yg&anker=Zefeb92d093a9fbf8b7c983722bdbb10d\" data-learningcard-id=\"4N03Yg\" data-anker=\"Zefeb92d093a9fbf8b7c983722bdbb10d\" data-section-id=\"mlcVxc0\" data-sememe-id=\"7h042f\">FAST</a>, CT delays definitive management and is inappropriate.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>Observation with serial labs may be appropriate in stable patients with suspected <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Bh0zTf&anker=Zfdae7b2ea943f3b332fdf4c3cf7cb8c3\" data-learningcard-id=\"Bh0zTf\" data-anker=\"Zfdae7b2ea943f3b332fdf4c3cf7cb8c3\">splenic injury</a>. However, this patient is unstable and requires immediate intervention.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) CORRECT:</h4>Correct -- This patient has <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=KT0U72&anker=Z755ac88bb64f9363cd02e1d26ffc61a4\" data-learningcard-id=\"KT0U72\" data-anker=\"Z755ac88bb64f9363cd02e1d26ffc61a4\" data-sememe-id=\"oP00fT\">splenomegaly</a> from recent <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Lf0w52&anker=Z396e86e88d3315f2dd9b99cf38d0942c\" data-learningcard-id=\"Lf0w52\" data-anker=\"Z396e86e88d3315f2dd9b99cf38d0942c\" data-sememe-id=\"Cj0qcT\">EBV infection</a> and now presents with abdominal <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a> after <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=GL0B_g&anker=Z59ef0ec37acf97d349b2195aaba30bb2\" data-learningcard-id=\"GL0B_g\" data-anker=\"Z59ef0ec37acf97d349b2195aaba30bb2\" data-section-id=\"qkcCKc0\">blunt abdominal trauma</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=rM0fJg&anker=Zb5022b8fa3fa419ab039a0f8d70866a2\" data-learningcard-id=\"rM0fJg\" data-anker=\"Zb5022b8fa3fa419ab039a0f8d70866a2\" data-section-id=\"oVc0vY0\" data-sememe-id=\"nGb7-E\">hypotension</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=rM0fJg&anker=Z3ae4e1e5581c7405590e65b57fa82021\" data-learningcard-id=\"rM0fJg\" data-anker=\"Z3ae4e1e5581c7405590e65b57fa82021\" data-section-id=\"KVcUvY0\" data-sememe-id=\"lNbvY8\">tachycardia</a>, and free <span data-sememe-id=\"0OceIc0\">intraperitoneal</span> fluid on <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4N03Yg&anker=Zefeb92d093a9fbf8b7c983722bdbb10d\" data-learningcard-id=\"4N03Yg\" data-anker=\"Zefeb92d093a9fbf8b7c983722bdbb10d\" data-section-id=\"mlcVxc0\" data-sememe-id=\"7h042f\">FAST</a>. These findings are consistent with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Bh0zTf&anker=Zd4d2c7ba6683324dfbcbdd8aeb0e356b\" data-learningcard-id=\"Bh0zTf\" data-anker=\"Zd4d2c7ba6683324dfbcbdd8aeb0e356b\" data-section-id=\"dcdoYK0\" data-sememe-id=\"YxYnEr\">splenic rupture</a>. The appropriate next step is urgent surgical consultation for <span data-sememe-id=\"u1bpis\">laparotomy</span>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=2M0TLg&anker=Zc708b1fe0f461e690573be05eb7425de\" data-learningcard-id=\"2M0TLg\" data-anker=\"Zc708b1fe0f461e690573be05eb7425de\" data-section-id=\"VXWGCP0\" data-sememe-id=\"igYJEo\">Platelet transfusion</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ln0vtg&anker=Z09c9e2d4a95bbada9230220c9d53e26d\" data-learningcard-id=\"ln0vtg\" data-anker=\"Z09c9e2d4a95bbada9230220c9d53e26d\">hematology</a> follow-up are inappropriate. The patient’s acute instability is due to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Bh0zTf&anker=Zd4d2c7ba6683324dfbcbdd8aeb0e356b\" data-learningcard-id=\"Bh0zTf\" data-anker=\"Zd4d2c7ba6683324dfbcbdd8aeb0e356b\" data-section-id=\"dcdoYK0\" data-sememe-id=\"YxYnEr\">splenic rupture</a>, not chronic <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=KT0U72&anker=Za0e26081e098a15167d39b7194c5e467\" data-learningcard-id=\"KT0U72\" data-anker=\"Za0e26081e098a15167d39b7194c5e467\" data-section-id=\"cJXaG_\" data-sememe-id=\"GoaBWl\">hypersplenism</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=km0mfg&anker=Z3733d22ef7bb87f743207060acda0451\" data-learningcard-id=\"km0mfg\" data-anker=\"Z3733d22ef7bb87f743207060acda0451\" data-section-id=\"Pq1WA30\" data-sememe-id=\"8AbOlw\">Corticosteroids</a> are not indicated in splenic trauma. The immediate priority is surgical intervention for life-threatening hemorrhage.</div>",
